<div>
<p>In this section, we'll take a look at specific business rules that may be helpful to a number of Service Management Automation X administrators. You may find a business rule that meets your rules exactly, or you might find that you can modify one of these examples slightly to meet the functionality that you need.</p>

<p><strong>Examples</strong></p>

<ul>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_1">Remove a value from a list using a rendering rule</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_2">Set a field to a group that will be moved when dev2prod runs</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_3">Make an entity read only after it has been closed </a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_4">Add the date and time in a readable format to a comment</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_5">Only display 3rd level Record Categories on an Incident/Request/Change</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_6">Concatenate text contained in two different fields into one</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_7">Suggest solutions for the Service desk group using the union function</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_8">Suggest solutions to set the Service desk group using the union and intersect functions</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_9">Send notification to first non-empty recipient</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_10">Sending Parent Entity information in Approval or Task emails</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://docs.microfocus.com/itom/SMAX:2020.02/PN/xc_bre_example_11">Passing parameters to notification templates</a></li>
</ul>

